initConnection

public void initConnection(byte[] appletID,
                           int readerIndex)
Initializes the secure channel connection with the Applet specified by appletID and Secure element specified by readerIndex

This method has a long running task. When the long running task completes the secure channel status listener is notified with a callback method ISEServiceStatusListener.scInitialized()

Parameters:
appletID - Applet ID
readerIndex - index of the terminal that the secure element is connected to

changePasswordandUserID

public void changePasswordandUserID(byte[] userID,
                                    byte[] newUserID,
                                    byte[] password,
                                    byte[] newPassword)
Changes userID and password based on the specified parameters. This method can be called only after the long running task of initConnection method is completed

This method does not check previous current values of userID and password. If only change of password is desired, userID and newUserID should have the same value

This method has a long running task. When the long running task completes the secure channel status listener is notified with a callback method IChannelStatusListener.passwordChanged()

Parameters:
userID - the current user ID
newUserID - a new user ID or current user ID
password - the current password
newPassword - a new password or current password

authenticate

public void authenticate(byte[] userID,
                         byte[] password)
Performs authentication using the specified userID and password, and initializes the secure channel session. Can be called only after the long running task of initConnection method is completed

This method has a long running task. When the long running task completes the secure channel status listener is notified with a callback method IChannelStatusListener.scInitialized()

Parameters:
userID - user ID
password - password

encodeAndSend

public byte[] encodeAndSend(CommandApdu commandApdu)
Constructs a ISO/IEC 7816-4 Secure Messaging Command APDU (ETSI TS 102 176-2 format) for commandAPDU and returns a decoded response data

This method handles all Secure Messaging related processing on the Command APDU and Response APDU. If the verification of the incoming ResponseAPDU fails, it returns the status word of the response

Parameters:
commandApdu - a CommandAPDU to be encoded
Returns:
decoded response data if the response is verified, otherwise status word of the response
